Keeper (password manager)|Keeper]] compiled its own list of the 25 most common passwords in 2016, from 25 million passwords leaked in data breaches that year.<ref name=keeper2016list>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/technology/2017/01/16/worlds-common-passwords-revealed-using/|title=The world's most common passwords revealed: Are you using them?|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=January 16, 2017|last=McGoogan|first=Cara}}</ref>\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Top 25 most common passwords according to Keeper\n! Rank\n! 2016<ref name=keeper2016list/>\n|-\n| align=center| 1\n| align=left| 123456\n|-\n| align=center| 2\n| align=left| 12345679\n|-\n| align=center| 3\n| align=left| qwerty\n|-\n| align=center| 4\n| align=left| 12345678\n|-\n| align=center| 5\n| align=left| 111111\n|-\n| align=center| 6\n| align=left| 1234567890\n|-\n| align=center| 7\n| align=left| 1234567\n|-\n| align=center| 8\n| align=left| password\n|-\n| align=center| 9\n| align=left| 123123\n|-\n| align=center| 10\n| align=left| 987654321\n|-\n| align=center| 11\n| align=left| qwertyuiop\n|-\n| align=center| 12\n| align=left| mynoob\n|-\n| align=center| 13\n| align=left| 123321\n|-\n| align=center| 14\n| align=left| 666666\n|-\n| align=center| 15\n| align=left| 18atcskd2w\n|-\n| align=center| 16\n| align=left| 7777777\n|-\n| align=center| 17\n| align=left| 1q2w3e4r\n|-\n| align=center| 18\n| align=left| 654321\n|-\n| align=center| 19\n| align=left| 555555\n|-\n| align=center| 20\n| align=left| 3rjs1la7qe\n|-\n| align=center| 21\n| align=left| google\n|-\n| align=center| 22\n| align=left| 1q2w3e4r5t\n|-\n| align=center| 23\n| align=left| 123qwe\n|-\n| align=center| 24\n| align=left| zxcvbnm\n|-\n| align=center| 25\n| align=left| 1q2w3e<br />\n|}\n\n===National Cyber Security Centre===\nThe [[National Cyber Security Centre (United Kingdom)|National Cyber Security Centre]] (NCSC) compiled its own list of the 20 most common passwords in 2019, from 100 million passwords leaked in data breaches this year.<ref name=NCSCList>{{cite web|url=https://www.technotification.com/2019/04/ncsc-worlds-most-hacked-passwords.html/|title=NCSC Reveals List Of World\u2019s Most Hacked Passwords|work=Technotification|date=April 23, 2019|last=Kapiswe|first=Subham|accessdate=April 24, 2019}}</ref>\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Top 20 most common passwords according to NCSC\n! Rank\n! 2019<ref name=NCSCList/>\n|-\n| align=center| 1\n| align=left| 123456\n|-\n| align=center| 2\n| align=left| 123456789\n|-\n| align=center| 3\n| align=left| qwerty\n|-\n| align=center| 4\n| align=left| password\n|-\n| align=center| 5\n| align=left| 1111111\n|-\n| align=center| 6\n| align=left| 12345678\n|-\n| align=center| 7\n| align=left| abc123\n|-\n| align=center| 8\n| align=left| 1234567\n|-\n| align=center| 9\n| align=left| password1\n|-\n| align=center| 10\n| align=left| 12345\n|-\n| align=center| 11\n| align=left| 1234567890\n|-\n| align=center| 12\n| align=left| 123123\n|-\n| align=center| 13\n| align=left| 000000\n|-\n| align=center| 14\n| align=left| Iloveyou\n|-\n| align=center| 15\n| align=left| 1234\n|-\n| align=center| 16\n| align=left| 1q2w3e4r5t\n|-\n| align=center| 17\n| align=left| Qwertyuiop\n|-\n| align=center| 18\n| align=left| 123\n|-\n| align=center| 19\n| align=left| Monkey\n|-\n| align=center| 20\n| align=left| Dragon\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Password cracking]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.teamsid.com/worst-passwords-2016/?nabe=5285852066611200:1 Worst passwords of 2016 (SplashData official website)]\n* [https://wiki.skullsecurity.org/index.php?title=Passwords Skullsecurity list of breached password collections]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Passwords}}\n[[Category:Security]]\n[[Category:Password authentication]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|list of common passwords}}\n{{use MDY dates|date=June 2017}}\nThis is a '''list of the most common [[password]]s''', discovered in various data breaches. Common passwords generally are not recommended on account of low [[password strength]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/technology/2016/01/26/most-common-passwords-revealed---and-theyre-ridiculously-easy-to/ | title=Do you have one of the most common passwords? They\u2019re ridiculously easy to guess | work=The Telegraph | date=March 23, 2016 | accessdate=May 1, 2017 | author=Titcomb, James}}</ref>\n\n==List==\n===SplashData===\nThe Worst Passwords List is an annual list of the 25 most common passwords from each year as produced by [[internet security]] firm SplashData.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/these-were-the-25-worst-passwords-of-2015/|title=These were the 25 worst passwords of 2015|work=CBS News|date=January 20, 2016|last=Mastroianni|first=Brian}}</ref> Since 2011, the firm has published the list based on data examined from millions of passwords leaked in data breaches, mostly in North America and Western Europe, over each year. In the 2016 edition, the 25 most common passwords made up more than 10% of the surveyed passwords, with the most common password of 2016, \"123456\", making up 4%.<ref name=splashdata2016/>\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Top 25 most common passwords by year according to SplashData\n! Rank\n! 2011<ref>{{cite web|url=http://techland.time.com/2011/11/22/the-25-most-popular-and-worst-passwords-of-2011/|title=The 25 Most Popular (and Worst) Passwords of 2011|work=TIME|date=November 22, 2011|last=Ho|first=Erica}}</ref>\n! 2012<ref>{{cite web|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2012/10/25/tech/web/worst-passwords-2012/|title=The 25 worst passwords of 2012|work=CNN|date=October 25, 2012|last=Waxman|first=Olivia B.}}</ref>\n! 2013<ref name=splashdata2013>{{cite web|url=http://www.pcworld.com/article/2089244/the-25-worst-passwords-of-2013-password-gets-dethroned.html|title=The 25 worst passwords of 2013: 'password' gets dethroned|work=[[PC World]]|date=January 20, 2014|last=Newman|first=Jared}}</ref>\n! 2014<ref>{{cite web|url=http://time.com/3672431/worst-passwords/|title=These Are The 25 Worst Passwords of 2014|work=TIME|date=January 20, 2015|last=Waxman|first=Olivia}}</ref>\n! 2015<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitaltrends.com/web/splashdata-worst-passwords/|title=Wookie mistake: \u2018starwars\u2019 is now one of the world\u2019s 25 worst passwords|work=[[Digital Trends]]||date=January 19, 2016|last=Chang|first=Lulu}}</ref>\n! 2016<ref name=splashdata2016>{{cite web|url=http://time.com/4639791/worst-passwords-2016/|title=The 25 Worst Passwords You Should Never Use|work=TIME|date=January 23, 2017|last=Bruner|first=Raisa}}</ref>\n! 2017<ref name=splashdata2017>{{cite web|url=http://fortune.com/2017/12/19/the-25-most-used-hackable-passwords-2017-star-wars-freedom/|title=\nThe 25 Most Common Passwords of 2017 Include \u2018Star Wars\u2019|work=FORTUNE|date=December 19, 2017|last=Korosec|first=Kirsten}}</ref>\n! 2018<ref name=splashdata2018>{{cite web|url=https://gizmodo.com/the-25-most-popular-passwords-of-2018-will-make-you-fee-1831052705|title=\nThe 25 Most Popular Passwords of 2018 Will Make You Feel Like a Security Genius|work=Gizmodo|date=December 13, 2018|last=Ehrenkranz|first=\nMelanie}}</ref>\n! 2019<ref name=splashdata2019>{{cite web|url=https://gizmodo.com/its-time-to-nervously-mock-the-50-worst-passwords-of-th-1840514905|title=\nIt's Time to Nervously Mock the 50 Worst Passwords of the Year|work=Gizmodo|date=December 18, 2019|last=Keck|first=\nCatie}}</ref>\n|-\n| align=center| 1\n| align=left| password\n| align=left| password\n| align=left| 123456\n| align=left| 123456\n| align=left| 123456\n| align=left| 123456\n| align=left| 123456\n| align=left| 123456\n| align=left| 123456\n|-\n| align=center| 2\n| align=left| 123456\n| align=left| 123456\n| align=left| password\n| align=left| password\n| align=left| password\n| align=left| password\n| align=left| password\n| align=left| password\n| align=left| 123456789\n|-\n| align=center| 3\n| align=left| 12345678\n| align=left| 12345678\n| align=left| 12