\n|1 : 6\n|-\n|''[[Lobster]], cooked''\n|{{Citation needed | date = February 2019}}\n|4 oz<br/>(113 g)\n|6\n|120\n|1 : 20\n|-\n|''[[Bluefish]], fresh and frozen, cooked''\n|{{Citation needed | date = February 2019}}\n|4 oz<br/>(113 g)\n|300\n|1700\n|1 : 5.6\n|-\n|''[[Salmon]], canned, drained''\n|{{Citation needed | date = February 2019}}\n|4 oz<br/>(113 g)\n|200\n|2200\n|1 : 11\n|-\n|''[[Smelts|Smelt]], rainbow''\n|{{Citation needed | date = February 2019}}\n|4 oz<br/>(113 g)\n|200\n|500\n|1 : 2.5\n|-\n|''[[Scallops]], Maine, fresh and frozen, cooked''\n|{{Citation needed | date = February 2019}}\n|4 oz<br/>(113 g)\n|100\n|500\n|1 : 5\n|-\n|[[Pacific herring]]\n|<ref>{{cite web | url = https://nutritiondata.self.com/facts/finfish-and-shellfish-products/4219/2 | title = Fish, herring, Pacific, cooked, dry heat Nutrition Facts & Calories | accessdate = 2019-02-15 | publisher = Self Nutrition Data, Cond\u00e9 Nast | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20180612054223/http://nutritiondata.self.com/facts/finfish-and-shellfish-products/4219/2 | archivedate = 2018-06-12 }}</ref>\n|100 g\n|246\n|2418\n|1 : 9.8\n|-\n|}\n\n==Nuts and seeds==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" width=89%\n|- bgcolor=\" #CCCCCC\"\n! width=30% | Food !! width=10% | Citation !! width=9% | Serving Size (g) !! width=9% ! data-sort-type=\"number\" |Omega-6 (mg)!! width=9% ! data-sort-type=\"number\" | Omega-3 (mg)!! width=25% ! data-sort-type=\"number\"| Omega-6 : Omega-3 ratio\n|-\n|''[[Almonds]], dry roasted''\n|<ref>{{cite web | url = http://nutritiondata.self.com/facts/nut-and-seed-products/3085/2 | title = Nuts, almonds [Includes USDA commodity food A256, A264] Nutrition Facts & Calories | publisher = Self Nutrition Data, Cond\u00e9 Nast | accessdate = 2019-02-15 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20190114081700/https://nutritiondata.self.com/facts/nut-and-seed-products/3085/2 | archivedate = 2019-01-14 }}</ref>\n|100\n|12065\n|6\n|2010.8 : 1\n|-\n|''[[Cashews]]''\n|<ref>{{cite web | 