{"title_page": "Diocese of Nidaros", "text_new": "{{for|the medieval Catholic archdiocese|Archdiocese of Nidaros}}\n{{Infobox diocese\n|jurisdiction = Diocese\n|name         = Nidaros\n|local        = {{lang|no|Nidaros bisped\u00f8mme}}\n|image        = Nidaros cathedral Trondheim 2009 1.JPG\n|caption      = [[Nidaros Cathedral]] in [[Trondheim]]\n|country      = [[Norway]]\n|territory    = [[Tr\u00f8ndelag]] county\n|denomination = [[Church of Norway]]\n|established  = 1068 \n|bishop       = [[Herborg Finnset]]\n|cathedral    = [[Nidaros Cathedral]]\n|deaneries    = 10 ''prosti''\n|parishes     = 134\n|members      = 357,914\n|map          = Dioceses Church of Norway.svg\n|map_caption  = Location of the Diocese of Nidaros\n|website      = [http://www.kirken.no/nidaros kirken.no/nidaros]\n}}\n\n'''Nidaros''' is a [[diocese]] in the [[Lutheran]] [[Church of Norway]]. It covers [[Tr\u00f8ndelag]] county in [[Central Norway]] and its cathedral city is [[Trondheim]], which houses the well-known [[Nidaros Cathedral]].  The diocese is divided into 10 [[deanery|deaneries]] ''(prosti)''.  Since 10 September 2017, the Bishop of Nidaros is [[Herborg Finnset]] who took over from the Bishop [[Tor Singsaas]] who retired.  The [[Preses (Church of Norway)|Bishop Preses]] is also based at the [[Nidaros Cathedral]] and serves as the dean of the [[Nidaros domprosti]] (deanery) in [[Trondheim]]. \n\n==History==\nThe diocese of Nidaros was established in 1068. It originally covered the (modern) counties of [[Tr\u00f8ndelag]], [[Nordland]], [[Troms]], and [[Finnmark]], along with the regions of [[Nordm\u00f8re]] and [[Romsdal]] (in [[M\u00f8re og Romsdal]] county) and [[H\u00e4rjedalen]] (in [[Sweden]]), and also the northern part of [[\u00d8sterdalen]] ([[Tynset]], [[Tolga, Norway|Tolga]], and [[Os, Hedmark|Os]]). The region of [[Sunnm\u00f8re]] (in [[M\u00f8re og Romsdal]]) was transferred from [[Diocese of Bj\u00f8rgvin]] to the new [[Archdiocese of Nidaros]] some time after 1152 \u2013 to secure it more income.\n\nThe northern part of \u00d8sterdalen was transferred to the [[Diocese of Oslo]] some time after 1537. The province of [[J\u00e4mtland]] was transferred from [[Diocese of Uppsala]] to Nidaros in 1570. The region of Sunnm\u00f8re was transferred (back) from Nidaros to the Diocese of Bj\u00f8rgvin in 1622. The provinces of J\u00e4mtland and H\u00e4rjedalen were lost to [[Sweden]] in 1645. [[Northern Norway]] was established as a diocese of its own in 1804 (formally first in 1844). The parish of [[Innset, S\u00f8r-Tr\u00f8ndelag|Innset]] was transferred from [[Diocese of Hamar]] to Nidaros in 1966. The regions of Nordm\u00f8re and Romsdal (together with Sunnm\u00f8re from Bj\u00f8rgvin) were established as a diocese of its own ([[Diocese of M\u00f8re]]) in 1983.\n\n==Structure==\n{{see also|List of churches in Tr\u00f8ndelag}}\nThe Diocese of Nidaros is divided into ten [[deanery|deaneries]] ({{lang-no|Prosti}}).  Each one corresponds to several municipalities in the diocese.  Each municipality is further divided into one or more [[parish]]es which each contain one or more congregations. \n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Deanery (''Prosti'') !! Municipalities\n|-\n| [[Nidaros domprosti]]||[[Trondheim]]\n|-\n| [[Heimdal og By\u00e5sen prosti]]||[[Trondheim]]\n|-\n| [[Strinda prosti]]||[[Trondheim]]\n|-\n| [[Fosen prosti]]||[[Indre Fosen]], [[Osen]], [[\u00d8rland]], [[\u00c5fjord]]\n|-\n| [[Orkdal prosti]]||[[Fr\u00f8ya, Tr\u00f8ndelag|Fr\u00f8ya]], [[Heim, Norway|Heim]], [[Hitra]], [[Orkland]], [[Skaun]]\n|-\n| [[Gauldal prosti]]||[[Holt\u00e5len]], [[Melhus]], [[Midtre Gauldal]], [[Oppdal]], [[Rennebu]], [[R\u00f8ros]]\n|-\n| [[Stj\u00f8rdal prosti]]||[[Malvik]], [[Mer\u00e5ker]], [[Selbu]], [[Stj\u00f8rdal]], [[Tydal]]\n|-\n| [[S\u00f8r-Innherad prosti]]||[[Frosta]], [[Levanger]], [[Verdal]]\n|-\n| [[Nord-Innherad prosti]]||[[Inder\u00f8y]], [[Namsos]], [[Sn\u00e5sa]], [[Steinkjer]]\n|-\n| [[Namdal prosti]]||[[Flatanger]], [[Grong]], [[H\u00f8ylandet]], [[Leka, Norway|Leka]], [[Lierne]], [[Namsos]], [[Namsskogan]], [[N\u00e6r\u00f8ysund]], [[Overhalla]], [[R\u00f8yrvik]]\n|}\n\n==Bishops==\nThe bishops of Nidaros since the [[Protestant Reformation]] when Norway switched from [[Catholicism]] to [[Lutheranism]]:\n{{div col begin}}\n*1546\u20131548 [[Torbj\u00f8rn Bratt]] \n*1549\u20131578 [[Hans Gaas]]  \n*1578\u20131595 [[Hans Mogenss\u00f8n]]  \n*1596\u20131617 [[Isak Gr\u00f8nbech]]  \n*1618\u20131622 [[Anders Arrebo]]  \n*1622\u20131642 [[Peder Skjelderup]]  \n*1643\u20131672 [[Erik Bredal]] \n*1672\u20131672 [[Arnold de Fine]] \n*1673\u20131678 [[Erik Eriksen Pontoppidan d.e.]]  \n*1678\u20131688 [[Christopher Hanssen Schletter]]  \n*1689\u20131731 [[Peder Krog]]  \n*1731\u20131743 [[Eiler Hansen Hagerup]] \n*1743\u20131748 [[Ludvig Harboe]]  \n*1748\u20131758 [[Frederik Nannestad]]  \n*1758\u20131773 [[Johan Ernst Gunnerus]] \n*1773\u20131789 [[Marcus Fredrik Bang]] \n*1788\u20131803 [[Johan Christian Sch\u00f8nheyder]]  \n*1804\u20131842 [[Peder Olivarius Bugge]]  \n*1843\u20131849 [[Hans Riddervold]] \n*1849\u20131860 [[Hans J\u00f8rgen Darre]] \n*1861\u20131883 [[Andreas Grimelund]] \n*1884\u20131892 [[Niels Laache]] \n*1892\u20131905 [[Johannes Skaar|Johannes Nilss\u00f8n Skaar]] \n*1905\u20131909 [[Vilhelm Andreas Wexelsen]] \n*1909\u20131923 [[Peter W. K. B\u00f8ckman Sr.]] \n*1923\u20131928 [[Jens Gran Gleditsch]] \n*1928\u20131942 [[Johan Nicolai St\u00f8ren]] \n*1945\u20131960 [[Arne Fjellbu]]  \n*1960\u20131979 [[Tord Godal]]  \n*1979\u20131991 [[Kristen Kyrre Bremer]] \n*1991\u20132008 [[Finn Wagle]] \n*2008\u20132017 [[Tor Singsaas]]<ref>{{cite news|first1=H\u00e5kon|last1=Jacobsen|last2=Jonassen|first2=Trine H\u00f8klie|title=Her er den nye biskopen in Nidaros|url=http://www.adressa.no/nyheter/trondheim/article1107048.ece|publisher=[[Adressavisen]]|location=Trondheim|accessdate=2008-06-27|language=Norwegian}}</ref>\n*2017\u2013present [[Herborg Finnset]] \n{{div col end}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Lutheran dioceses and archdioceses]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Bishops of Norway}}\n\n{{coord|63.4269|10.3969|region:NO|display=title}}\n{{authority control}}\n[[Category:Church of Norway dioceses|Nidaros]]\n[[Category:Organisations based in Trondheim]]\n[[Category:1068 establishments in Europe]]\n[[Category:11th-century establishments in Norway]]\n[[Category:Former Catholic dioceses in Sweden]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the medieval Catholic archdiocese|Archdiocese of Nidaros}}\n{{Infobox diocese\n|jurisdiction = Diocese\n|name         = Nidaros\n|local        = {{lang|no|Nidaros bisped\u00f8mme}}\n|image        = Nidaros cathedral Trondheim 2009 1.JPG\n|caption      = [[Nidaros Cathedral]] in [[Trondheim]]\n|country      = [[Norway]]\n|territory    = [[Tr\u00f8ndelag]] county\n|denomination = [[Church of Norway]]\n|established  = 1068 \n|bishop       = [[Herborg Finnset]]\n|cathedral    = [[Nidaros Cathedral]]\n|deaneries    = 10 ''prosti''\n|parishes     = 134\n|members      = 357,914\n|map          = Dioceses Church of Norway.svg\n|map_caption  = Location of the Diocese of Nidaros\n|website      = [http://www.kirken.no/nidaros kirken.no/nidaros]\n}}\n\n'''Nidaros''' is a [[diocese]] in the [[Lutheran]] [[Church of Norway]]. It covers [[Tr\u00f8ndelag]] county in [[Central Norway]] and its cathedral city is [[Trondheim]], which houses the well-known [[Nidaros Cathedral]].  The diocese is divided into 10 [[deanery|deaneries]] ''(prosti)''.  Since 10 September 2017, the Bishop of Nidaros is [[Herborg Finnset]] who took over from the Bishop [[Tor Singsaas]] who retired.  The [[Preses (Church of Norway)|Bishop Preses]] is also based at the [[Nidaros Cathedral]] and serves as the dean of the [[Nidaros domprosti]] (deanery) in [[Trondheim]]. \n\n==History==\nThe diocese of Nidaros was established in 1068. It originally covered the (modern) counties of [[Tr\u00f8ndelag]], [[Nordland]], [[Troms]], and [[Finnmark]], along with the regions of [[Nordm\u00f8re]] and [[Romsdal]] (in [[M\u00f8re og Romsdal]] county) and [[H\u00e4rjedalen]] (in [[Sweden]]), and also the northern part of [[\u00d8sterdalen]] ([[Tynset]], [[Tolga, Norway|Tolga]], and [[Os, Hedmark|Os]]). The region of [[Sunnm\u00f8re]] (in [[M\u00f8re og Romsdal]]) was transferred from [[Diocese of Bj\u00f8rgvin]] to the new [[Archdiocese of Nidaros]] some time after 1152 \u2013 to secure it more income.\n\nThe northern part of \u00d8sterdalen was transferred to the [[Diocese of Oslo]] some time after 1537. The province of [[J\u00e4mtland]] was transferred from [[Diocese of Uppsala]] to Nidaros in 1570. The region of Sunnm\u00f8re was transferred (back) from Nidaros to the Diocese of Bj\u00f8rgvin in 1622. The provinces of J\u00e4mtland and H\u00e4rjedalen were lost to [[Sweden]] in 1645. [[Northern Norway]] was established as a diocese of its own in 1804 (formally first in 1844). The parish of [[Innset, S\u00f8r-Tr\u00f8ndelag|Innset]] was transferred from [[Diocese of Hamar]] to Nidaros in 1966. The regions of Nordm\u00f8re and Romsdal (together with Sunnm\u00f8re from Bj\u00f8rgvin) were established as a diocese of its own ([[Diocese of M\u00f8re]]) in 1983.\n\n==Structure==\n{{see also|List of churches in Tr\u00f8ndelag}}\nThe Diocese of Nidaros is divided into ten [[deanery|deaneries]] ({{lang-no|Prosti}}).  Each one corresponds to several municipalities in the diocese.  Each municipality is further divided into one or more [[parish]]es which each contain one or more congregations. \n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Deanery (''Prosti'') !! Municipalities\n|-\n| [[Nidaros domprosti]]||[[Trondheim]]\n|-\n| [[Heimdal og By\u00e5sen prosti]]||[[Trondheim]]\n|-\n| [[Strinda prosti]]||[[Trondheim]]\n|-\n| [[Fosen prosti]]||[[Indre Fosen]], [[Osen]], [[\u00d8rland]], [[\u00c5fjord]]\n|-\n| [[Orkdal prosti]]||[[Fr\u00f8ya, Tr\u00f8ndelag|Fr\u00f8ya]], [[Heim, Norway|Heim]], [[Hitra]], [[Orkland]], [[Skaun]]\n|-\n| [[Gauldal prosti]]||[[Holt\u00e5len]], [[Melhus]], [[Midtre Gauldal]], [[Oppdal]], [[Rennebu]], [[R\u00f8ros]]\n|-\n| [[Stj\u00f8rdal prosti]]||[[Malvik]], [[Mer\u00e5ker]], [[Selbu]], [[Stj\u00f8rdal]], [[Tydal]]\n|-\n| [[S\u00f8r-Innherad prosti]]||[[Frosta]], [[Levanger]], [[Verdal]]\n|-\n| [[Nord-Innherad prosti]]||[[Inder\u00f8y]], [[Namsos]], [[Sn\u00e5sa]], [[Steinkjer]]\n|-\n| [[Namdal prosti]]||[[Flatanger]], [[Grong]], [[H\u00f8ylandet]], [[Leka, Norway|Leka]], [[Lierne]], [[Namsos]], [[Namsskogan]], [[N\u00e6r\u00f8y]], [[Overhalla]], [[R\u00f8yrvik]], [[Vikna]]\n|}\n\n==Bishops==\nThe bishops of Nidaros since the [[Protestant Reformation]] when Norway switched from [[Catholicism]] to [[Lutheranism]]:\n{{div col begin}}\n*1546\u20131548 [[Torbj\u00f8rn Bratt]] \n*1549\u20131578 [[Hans Gaas]]  \n*1578\u20131595 [[Hans Mogenss\u00f8n]]  \n*1596\u20131617 [[Isak Gr\u00f8nbech]]  \n*1618\u20131622 [[Anders Arrebo]]  \n*1622\u20131642 [[Peder Skjelderup]]  \n*1643\u20131672 [[Erik Bredal]] \n*1672\u20131672 [[Arnold de Fine]] \n*1673\u20131678 [[Erik Eriksen Pontoppidan d.e.]]  \n*1678\u20131688 [[Christopher Hanssen Schletter]]  \n*1689\u20131731 [[Peder Krog]]  \n*1731\u20131743 [[Eiler Hansen Hagerup]] \n*1743\u20131748 [[Ludvig Harboe]]  \n*1748\u20131758 [[Frederik Nannestad]]  \n*1758\u20131773 [[Johan Ernst Gunnerus]] \n*1773\u20131789 [[Marcus Fredrik Bang]] \n*1788\u20131803 [[Johan Christian Sch\u00f8nheyder]]  \n*1804\u20131842 [[Peder Olivarius Bugge]]  \n*1843\u20131849 [[Hans Riddervold]] \n*1849\u20131860 [[Hans J\u00f8rgen Darre]] \n*1861\u20131883 [[Andreas Grimelund]] \n*1884\u20131892 [[Niels Laache]] \n*1892\u20131905 [[Johannes Skaar|Johannes Nilss\u00f8n Skaar]] \n*1905\u20131909 [[Vilhelm Andreas Wexelsen]] \n*1909\u20131923 [[Peter W. K. B\u00f8ckman Sr.]] \n*1923\u20131928 [[Jens Gran Gleditsch]] \n*1928\u20131942 [[Johan Nicolai St\u00f8ren]] \n*1945\u20131960 [[Arne Fjellbu]]  \n*1960\u20131979 [[Tord Godal]]  \n*1979\u20131991 [[Kristen Kyrre Bremer]] \n*1991\u20132008 [[Finn Wagle]] \n*2008\u20132017 [[Tor Singsaas]]<ref>{{cite news|first1=H\u00e5kon|last1=Jacobsen|last2=Jonassen|first2=Trine H\u00f8klie|title=Her er den nye biskopen in Nidaros|url=http://www.adressa.no/nyheter/trondheim/article1107048.ece|publisher=[[Adressavisen]]|location=Trondheim|accessdate=2008-06-27|language=Norwegian}}</ref>\n*2017\u2013present [[Herborg Finnset]] \n{{div col end}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Lutheran dioceses and archdioceses]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Bishops of Norway}}\n\n{{coord|63.4269|10.3969|region:NO|display=title}}\n{{authority control}}\n[[Category:Church of Norway dioceses|Nidaros]]\n[[Category:Organisations based in Trondheim]]\n[[Category:1068 establishments in Europe]]\n[[Category:11th-century establishments in Norway]]\n[[Category:Former Catholic dioceses in Sweden]]\n", "name_user": "Redriv", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eStructure:changed Naeroy to Naeroysund and deleted Vikna", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diocese_of_Nidaros"}
{"title_page": "Markus Berger", "text_new": "{{short description|Austrian professional footballer|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Markus Berger\n| image = Markus Berger 04.12.2013.jpg\n| caption = Berger (left) in action for [[FC Chornomorets Odesa|Chornomorets]] \n| fullname = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1985|1|21|df=y}}<ref name=Profile>{{cite web|url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/m-berger/academica/1586-128-1286-24043|title=M. Berger|publisher=Mais Futebol|language=pt|accessdate=21 April 2020}}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Salzburg]], [[Austria]]<ref name=Profile/>\n| height = {{convert|1.86|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}}<ref name=Profile/>\n| position = [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|Centre back]]\n| currentclub = [[Salzburger AK 1914|SAK 1914]]\n| clubnumber = 5\n| youthyears1 = 1993\u20131999 | youthclubs1 = [[SV Austria Salzburg|Austria Salzburg]]\n| youthyears2 = 1999\u20132002 | youthclubs2 = [[VfB Stuttgart|Stuttgart]]\n| youthyears3 = 2002\u20132004 | youthclubs3 = [[Eintracht Frankfurt]]\n| years1 = 2004\u20132007 | clubs1 = [[SV Ried|Ried]] | caps1 = 61 | goals1 = 1\n| years2 = 2007\u20132011 | clubs2 = [[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Acad\u00e9mica de Coimbra \u2013 O.A.F.|Acad\u00e9mica]] | caps2 = 71 | goals2 = 5\n| years3 = 2012\u20132014 | clubs3 = [[FC Chornomorets Odesa|Chornomorets]] | caps3 = 52 | goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2014 | clubs4 = [[IK Start|Start]] | caps4 = 11 | goals4 = 1\n| years5 = 2014 | clubs5 = [[FC Ural Sverdlovsk Oblast|Ural]] | caps5 = 3 | goals5 = 0\n| years6 = 2015 | clubs6 = [[Gil Vicente F.C.|Gil Vicente]] | caps6 =  11 | goals6 = 1\n| years7 = 2015\u20132016 | clubs7 = [[C.D. Tondela|Tondela]] | caps7 = 3 | goals7 = 0\n| years8 = 2016\u20132018 | clubs8 = [[SV Gr\u00f6dig|Gr\u00f6dig]] | caps8 = 41 | goals8 = 3\n| years9 = 2018\u2013 | clubs9 = [[Salzburger AK 1914|SAK 1914]] | caps9 = 39 | goals9 = 3\n| totalcaps = | totalgoals = \n| nationalyears1 = 2004\u20132007 | nationalteam1 = [[Austria national under-21 football team|Austria U21]] | nationalcaps1 = 34 | nationalgoals1 = 0 \n| club-update = 25 October 2019\n}}\n'''Markus Berger''' (born 21 January 1985) is an Austrian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Salzburger AK 1914]] as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|central defender]].\n\n==Club career==\nHaving started his professional career at [[SV Ried]], Berger helping to promotion to the [[Austrian Football Bundesliga|Bundesliga]] in his first year, and played 14 games as the team finished in a best-ever runner-up position in [[2006\u201307 Austrian Football Bundesliga|2006\u201307]]. [[Primeira Liga]] side [[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Acad\u00e9mica de Coimbra \u2013 O.A.F.|Acad\u00e9mica de Coimbra]] signed him in July 2007, as a [[free agent]];<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.futebol365.pt/artigo/16885-academica-contratou-defesa-austriaco-markus-berger-ao-sv-ried/|title=Acad\u00e9mica contratou defesa austr\u00edaco Markus Berger ao SV Ried|trans-title=Acad\u00e9mica signed Austrian defender Markus Berger from SV Ried|publisher=Futebol 365|language=Portuguese|date=4 June 2007|accessdate=21 April 2020}}</ref> after going almost unnoticed throughout [[2007\u201308 Primeira Liga|the season]],<ref name=Renewal>{{cite web|url=https://www.futebol365.pt/artigo/27250-academica-markus-berger-renova-por-dois-anos/|title=Acad\u00e9mica: Markus Berger renova por dois anos|trans-title=Acad\u00e9mica: Markus Berger renews for two years|publisher=Futebol 365|language=Portuguese|date=15 January 2010|accessdate=21 April 2020}}</ref> he scored in his fifth match with the ''Students'' in a 3\u20130 away win against [[S.L. Benfica]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maisfutebol.iol.pt/benfica-academica-0-3-ficha|title=Benfica-Acad\u00e9mica, 0\u20133 (ficha)|trans-title=Benfica-Acad\u00e9mica, 0\u20133 (report)|publisher=Mais Futebol|language=Portuguese|date=11 April 2008|accessdate=7 June 2017}}</ref>\n\nBerger was first choice in his last two years with Acad\u00e9mica,<ref name=Renewal/> netting a combined four league goals in the process. During January 2009, he went on a trial period with [[Hibernian F.C.|Hibernian]] from the [[Scottish Premier League]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11781/4817929/hibs-look-at-berger|title=Hibs look at Berger|publisher=[[Sky Sports]]|date=19 January 2009|accessdate=21 April 2020}}</ref> and his agent later claimed that a loan deal had been agreed between the clubs with Hibs having the option to buy the player at the end of [[Scottish Premier League 2008\u201309|the campaign]] for [[Pound sterling|\u00a3]]500,000,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11065/4848498/hibs-agree-berger-loan|title=Hibs agree Berger loan|publisher=Sky Sports|first=Francisco|last=Acedo|date=25 January 2009|accessdate=21 April 2020}}</ref> but the move was not completed.\n\nOn 30 December 2011, after nearly 100 official appearances for Acad\u00e9mica, Berger penned a three-year contract at [[Ukrainian Premier League]]'s [[FC Chornomorets Odesa]]. At the start of March 2014, he left his team due to the civil unrest caused by the [[2014 Ukrainian revolution]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.kyivpost.com/content/ukraine/five-foreign-players-leave-football-club-chornomorets-because-of-situation-in-ukraine-338369.html|title=Five foreign players leave Football Club Chornomorets because of situation in Ukraine|newspaper=[[Kyiv Post]]|date=4 March 2014|accessdate=8 April 2014}}</ref> going on to sign for [[Tippeligaen]] club [[IK Start]] late into that month.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ikstart.no/news/article/1o8nd0r7q5w5g1awpac92qalum/title/start-henter-midtstopper|title=Start henter midtstopper|trans-title=Start acquire defender|publisher=IK Start|language=Norwegian|date=31 March 2014|accessdate=31 March 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141031105318/http://www.ikstart.no/news/article/1o8nd0r7q5w5g1awpac92qalum/title/start-henter-midtstopper|archivedate=31 October 2014}}</ref> He made his debut on 6 April in a 3\u20131 home victory over [[FK Haugesund]], in which he also scored his first goal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nrk.no/sport/fotball/tre-start-scoringar-pa-seks-minutt-1.11652422|title=Mjelde etter Start-magi: \u2013 Trudde nesten ikkje det eg s\u00e5g|trans-title=Report for Start magic: \u2013 Almost did not believe what I saw|publisher=[[NRK]]|language=Norwegian|date=6 April 2014|accessdate=21 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2014, after only a few months in Norway, Berger moved to the [[Russian Premier League]] with [[FC Ural Sverdlovsk Oblast]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fc-ural.ru/main/news/ural/2212/|script-title=ru:\u00ab\u0423\u0420\u0410\u041b\u00bb \u0417\u0410\u041a\u041b\u042e\u0427\u0418\u041b \u041a\u041e\u041d\u0422\u0420\u0410\u041a\u0422 \u0421 \u041c\u0410\u0420\u041a\u0423\u0421\u041e\u041c \u0411\u0415\u0420\u0413\u0415\u0420\u041e\u041c|trans-title=Ural signed a contract with Markus Berger|publisher=FC Ural|language=Russian|date=19 June 2014|accessdate=19 June 2014|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140622125724/http://www.fc-ural.ru/main/news/ural/2212/|archive-date=22 June 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.sportbox.ru/Vidy_sporta/Futbol/transfers/spbnews_NI464610_Ural-podpisal-chetverih-novichkov|script-title=ru:\u00ab\u0423\u0440\u0430\u043b\u00bb \u043f\u043e\u0434\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0430\u043b \u0447\u0435\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0440\u044b\u0445 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447\u043a\u043e\u0432|trans-title=Ural signed four new|publisher=Sportbox|language=Russian|date=28 June 2014|accessdate=10 July 2014}}</ref> However, in January of the following year, he returned to Portugal after signing with [[Gil Vicente F.C.]] until the end of [[2014\u201315 Primeira Liga|the season]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/futebol-nacional/interior/gil-vicente-anuncia-contratacao-do-defesa-markus-berger-4373114.html|title=Gil Vicente anuncia contrata\u00e7\u00e3o do defesa Markus Berger|trans-title=Gil Vicente announce signing of defender Markus Berger|newspaper=[[Di\u00e1rio de Not\u00edcias]]|first=Jo\u00e3o|last=Ruela|language=Portuguese|date=30 January 2015|accessdate=8 July 2015}}</ref>\n\nBerger agreed to a one-year deal with [[C.D. Tondela]] in early July 2015, after suffering relegation.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cdtondela.pt/noticias.asp?idnot=684|title=Markus Berger assina com o CD Tondela|trans-title=Markus Berger signs with CD Tondela|publisher=CD Tondela|language=Portuguese|date=5 July 2015|accessdate=8 July 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150709164047/http://www.cdtondela.pt/noticias.asp?idnot=684|archivedate=9 July 2015}}</ref> He returned to his country on 20 June 2016, joining [[Austrian Regional League West|Regional League West]] side [[SV Gr\u00f6dig]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.laola1.at/de/red/fussball/regionalligen/groedig-holt-markus-und-hans-peter-berger/|title=Gr\u00f6dig holt Hans-Peter und Markus Berger|trans-title=Gr\u00f6dig get Hans-Peter and Markus Berger|publisher=[[Laola1]]|language=German|date=20 June 2016|accessdate=7 June 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nBerger's older brother, [[Hans-Peter Berger|Hans-Peter]], was also a footballer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.salzburg24.at/markus-berger-wechselt-mit-bruder-hans-peter-zum-sv-groedig/4760278|title=Markus Berger wechselt mit Bruder Hans-Peter zum SV Gr\u00f6dig|trans-title=Markus Berger moves to SV Gr\u00f6dig with brother Hans-Peter|publisher=Salzburg 24|language=German|date=20 June 2016|accessdate=7 June 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n'''Acad\u00e9mica'''\n*[[Ta\u00e7a de Portugal]]: [[2011\u201312 Ta\u00e7a de Portugal|2011\u201312]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/amp/academica-percurso-notavel-ate-a-conquista-da-taca|title=Acad\u00e9mica: percurso not\u00e1vel at\u00e9 \u00e0 conquista da ta\u00e7a|trans-title=Acad\u00e9mica: remarkable run until the cup conquest|publisher=Mais Futebol|language=Portuguese|date=20 May 2012|accessdate=21 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{ForaDeJogo}}\n*{{Soccerway|markus-berger/10993}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Berger, Markus}}\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Salzburg]]\n[[Category:Austrian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Austrian Football Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:Austrian Football Second League players]]\n[[Category:SV Ried players]]\n[[Category:SV Gr\u00f6dig players]]\n[[Category:Primeira Liga players]]\n[[Category:Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Acad\u00e9mica de Coimbra \u2013 O.A.F. players]]\n[[Category:Gil Vicente F.C. players]]\n[[Category:C.D. Tondela players]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian Premier League players]]\n[[Category:FC Chornomorets Odesa players]]\n[[Category:Eliteserien players]]\n[[Category:IK Start players]]\n[[Category:Russian Premier League players]]\n[[Category:FC Ural Yekaterinburg players]]\n[[Category:Austria under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Austrian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Portugal]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Ukraine]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Norway]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Russia]]\n[[Category:Austrian expatriate sportspeople in Portugal]]\n[[Category:Austrian expatriate sportspeople in Ukraine]]\n[[Category:Austrian expatriate sportspeople in Norway]]\n[[Category:Austrian expatriate sportspeople in Russia]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Austrian professional footballer|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Markus Berger\n| image = Markus Berger 04.12.2013.jpg\n| caption = Berger (left) in action for [[FC Chornomorets Odesa|Chornomorets]] \n| fullname = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1985|1|21|df=y}}<ref name=Profile>{{cite web|url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/m-berger/academica/1586-128-1286-24043|title=M. Berger|publisher=Mais Futebol|language=pt|accessdate=21 April 2020}}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Salzburg]], [[Austria]]<ref name=Profile/>\n| height = {{convert|1.86|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}}<ref name=Profile/>\n| position = [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|Centre back]]\n| currentclub = [[Salzburger AK 1914|SAK 1914]]\n| clubnumber = 5\n| youthyears1 = 1993\u20131999 | youthclubs1 = [[SV Austria Salzburg|Austria Salzburg]]\n| youthyears2 = 1999\u20132002 | youthclubs2 = [[VfB Stuttgart|Stuttgart]]\n| youthyears3 = 2002\u20132004 | youthclubs3 = [[Eintracht Frankfurt]]\n| years1 = 2004\u20132007 | clubs1 = [[SV Ried|Ried]] | caps1 = 61 | goals1 = 1\n| years2 = 2007\u20132011 | clubs2 = [[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Acad\u00e9mica de Coimbra \u2013 O.A.F.|Acad\u00e9mica]] | caps2 = 71 | goals2 = 5\n| years3 = 2012\u20132014 | clubs3 = [[FC Chornomorets Odesa|Chornomorets]] | caps3 = 52 | goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2014 | clubs4 = [[IK Start|Start]] | caps4 = 11 | goals4 = 1\n| years5 = 2014 | clubs5 = [[FC Ural Sverdlovsk Oblast|Ural]] | caps5 = 3 | goals5 = 0\n| years6 = 2015 | clubs6 = [[Gil Vicente F.C.|Gil Vicente]] | caps6 =  11 | goals6 = 1\n| years7 = 2015\u20132016 | clubs7 = [[C.D. Tondela|Tondela]] | caps7 = 3 | goals7 = 0\n| years8 = 2016\u20132018 | clubs8 = [[SV Gr\u00f6dig|Gr\u00f6dig]] | caps8 = 41 | goals8 = 3\n| years9 = 2018\u2013 | clubs9 = [[Salzburger AK 1914|SAK 1914]] | caps9 = 39 | goals9 = 3\n| totalcaps = | totalgoals = \n| nationalyears1 = 2004\u20132007 | nationalteam1 = [[Austria national under-21 football team|Austria U21]] | nationalcaps1 = 34 | nationalgoals1 = 0 \n| club-update = 25 October 2019\n}}\n'''Markus Berger''' (born 21 January 1985) is an Austrian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Salzburger AK 1914]] as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|central defender]].\n\n==Club career==\nHaving started his professional career at [[SV Ried]], Berger helping to promotion to the [[Austrian Football Bundesliga|Bundesliga]] in his first year, and played 14 matches as the team finished in a best-ever runner-up position in the [[2006\u201307 Austrian Football Bundesliga|2006\u201307 season]]. [[Primeira Liga]] side [[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Acad\u00e9mica de Coimbra \u2013 O.A.F.|Acad\u00e9mica de Coimbra]] signed him in July 2007, as a [[free agent]];<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.futebol365.pt/artigo/16885-academica-contratou-defesa-austriaco-markus-berger-ao-sv-ried/|title=Acad\u00e9mica contratou defesa austr\u00edaco Markus Berger ao SV Ried|trans-title=Acad\u00e9mica signed Austrian defender Markus Berger from SV Ried|publisher=Futebol 365|language=Portuguese|date=4 June 2007|accessdate=21 April 2020}}</ref> after going almost unnoticed throughout [[2007\u201308 Primeira Liga|the campaign]],<ref name=Renewal>{{cite web|url=https://www.futebol365.pt/artigo/27250-academica-markus-berger-renova-por-dois-anos/|title=Acad\u00e9mica: Markus Berger renova por dois anos|trans-title=Acad\u00e9mica: Markus Berger renews for two years|publisher=Futebol 365|language=Portuguese|date=15 January 2010|accessdate=21 April 2020}}</ref> he scored in his fifth match with the ''Students'' in a 3\u20130 away win against [[S.L. Benfica]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maisfutebol.iol.pt/benfica-academica-0-3-ficha|title=Benfica-Acad\u00e9mica, 0\u20133 (ficha)|trans-title=Benfica-Acad\u00e9mica, 0\u20133 (report)|publisher=Mais Futebol|language=Portuguese|date=11 April 2008|accessdate=7 June 2017}}</ref>\n\nBerger was first-choice in his last two years with Acad\u00e9mica,<ref name=Renewal/> netting a combined four league goals in the process. During January 2009, he went on a trial period with [[Hibernian F.C.|Hibernian]] from the [[Scottish Premier League]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11781/4817929/hibs-look-at-berger|title=Hibs look at Berger|publisher=[[Sky Sports]]|date=19 January 2009|accessdate=21 April 2020}}</ref> and his agent later claimed that a loan deal had been agreed between the clubs with Hibs having the option to buy the player at the end of [[Scottish Premier League 2008\u201309|the season]] for [[Pound sterling|\u00a3]]500,000,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11065/4848498/hibs-agree-berger-loan|title=Hibs agree Berger loan|publisher=Sky Sports|first=Francisco|last=Acedo|date=25 January 2009|accessdate=21 April 2020}}</ref> but the move was not completed.\n\nOn 30 December 2011, after nearly 100 official appearances for Acad\u00e9mica, Berger penned a three-year contract at [[Ukrainian Premier League]]'s [[FC Chornomorets Odesa]]. At the start of March 2014, he left his team due to the civil unrest caused by the [[2014 Ukrainian revolution]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.kyivpost.com/content/ukraine/five-foreign-players-leave-football-club-chornomorets-because-of-situation-in-ukraine-338369.html|title=Five foreign players leave Football Club Chornomorets because of situation in Ukraine|newspaper=[[Kyiv Post]]|date=4 March 2014|accessdate=8 April 2014}}</ref> going on to sign for [[Tippeligaen]] club [[IK Start]] late into that month.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ikstart.no/news/article/1o8nd0r7q5w5g1awpac92qalum/title/start-henter-midtstopper|title=Start henter midtstopper|trans-title=Start acquire defender|publisher=IK Start|language=Norwegian|date=31 March 2014|accessdate=31 March 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141031105318/http://www.ikstart.no/news/article/1o8nd0r7q5w5g1awpac92qalum/title/start-henter-midtstopper|archivedate=31 October 2014}}</ref> He made his debut on 6 April in a 3\u20131 home victory over [[FK Haugesund]], in which he also scored his first goal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nrk.no/sport/fotball/tre-start-scoringar-pa-seks-minutt-1.11652422|title=Mjelde etter Start-magi: \u2013 Trudde nesten ikkje det eg s\u00e5g|trans-title=Report for Start magic: \u2013 Almost did not believe what I saw|publisher=[[NRK]]|language=Norwegian|date=6 April 2014|accessdate=21 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2014, after only a few months in Norway, Berger moved to the [[Russian Premier League]] with [[FC Ural Sverdlovsk Oblast]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fc-ural.ru/main/news/ural/2212/|script-title=ru:\u00ab\u0423\u0420\u0410\u041b\u00bb \u0417\u0410\u041a\u041b\u042e\u0427\u0418\u041b \u041a\u041e\u041d\u0422\u0420\u0410\u041a\u0422 \u0421 \u041c\u0410\u0420\u041a\u0423\u0421\u041e\u041c \u0411\u0415\u0420\u0413\u0415\u0420\u041e\u041c|trans-title=Ural signed a contract with Markus Berger|publisher=FC Ural|language=Russian|date=19 June 2014|accessdate=19 June 2014|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140622125724/http://www.fc-ural.ru/main/news/ural/2212/|archive-date=22 June 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.sportbox.ru/Vidy_sporta/Futbol/transfers/spbnews_NI464610_Ural-podpisal-chetverih-novichkov|script-title=ru:\u00ab\u0423\u0440\u0430\u043b\u00bb \u043f\u043e\u0434\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0430\u043b \u0447\u0435\u0442\u0432\u0435\u0440\u044b\u0445 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447\u043a\u043e\u0432|trans-title=Ural signed four new|publisher=Sportbox|language=Russian|date=28 June 2014|accessdate=10 July 2014}}</ref> However, in January of the following year, he returned to Portugal after signing with [[Gil Vicente F.C.]] until the end of [[2014\u201315 Primeira Liga|the season]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/futebol-nacional/interior/gil-vicente-anuncia-contratacao-do-defesa-markus-berger-4373114.html|title=Gil Vicente anuncia contrata\u00e7\u00e3o do defesa Markus Berger|trans-title=Gil Vicente announce signing of defender Markus Berger|newspaper=[[Di\u00e1rio de Not\u00edcias]]|first=Jo\u00e3o|last=Ruela|language=Portuguese|date=30 January 2015|accessdate=8 July 2015}}</ref>\n\nBerger agreed to a one-year deal with [[C.D. Tondela]] in early July 2015, after suffering relegation.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cdtondela.pt/noticias.asp?idnot=684|title=Markus Berger assina com o CD Tondela|trans-title=Markus Berger signs with CD Tondela|publisher=CD Tondela|language=Portuguese|date=5 July 2015|accessdate=8 July 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150709164047/http://www.cdtondela.pt/noticias.asp?idnot=684|archivedate=9 July 2015}}</ref> He returned to his country on 20 June 2016, joining [[Austrian Regional League West|Regional League West]] side [[SV Gr\u00f6dig]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.laola1.at/de/red/fussball/regionalligen/groedig-holt-markus-und-hans-peter-berger/|title=Gr\u00f6dig holt Hans-Peter und Markus Berger|trans-title=Gr\u00f6dig get Hans-Peter and Markus Berger|publisher=[[Laola1]]|language=German|date=20 June 2016|accessdate=7 June 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nBerger's older brother, [[Hans-Peter Berger|Hans-Peter]], was also a footballer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.salzburg24.at/markus-berger-wechselt-mit-bruder-hans-peter-zum-sv-groedig/4760278|title=Markus Berger wechselt mit Bruder Hans-Peter zum SV Gr\u00f6dig|trans-title=Markus Berger moves to SV Gr\u00f6dig with brother Hans-Peter|publisher=Salzburg 24|language=German|date=20 June 2016|accessdate=7 June 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n'''Acad\u00e9mica'''\n*[[Ta\u00e7a de Portugal]]: [[2011\u201312 Ta\u00e7a de Portugal|2011\u201312]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/amp/academica-percurso-notavel-ate-a-conquista-da-taca|title=Acad\u00e9mica: percurso not\u00e1vel at\u00e9 \u00e0 conquista da ta\u00e7a|trans-title=Acad\u00e9mica: remarkable run until the cup conquest|publisher=Mais Futebol|language=Portuguese|date=20 May 2012|accessdate=21 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{ForaDeJogo}}\n*{{Soccerway|markus-berger/10993}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Berger, Markus}}\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Salzburg]]\n[[Category:Austrian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[